1
00:00:24,652 --> 00:00:27,883
[ Narrator ] Mutation--
it is the key to our evolution.

2
00:00:27,955 --> 00:00:31,152
It has enabled us to evolve
from a single-celled organism...

3
00:00:31,225 --> 00:00:33,693
into the dominant species
on the planet.

4
00:00:33,761 --> 00:00:38,164
This process is slow and normally taking
thousands and thousands of years.

5
00:00:38,232 --> 00:00:42,293
But every few hundred millennia,
evolution leaps forward.

6
00:01:37,691 --> 00:01:40,353
[ Men Shouting ]

7
00:02:34,610 --> 00:02:37,545
[ Shouting In
Eastern European Language ]

8
00:02:52,194 --> 00:02:54,685
[ Woman Screaming ]

9
00:03:33,369 --> 00:03:36,429
[ Electricity Zapping ]

10
00:04:26,388 --> 00:04:29,380
Niagara Falls. Up...

11
00:04:29,458 --> 00:04:34,725
the Canadian Rockies, and then it's
only a few hundred miles to Anchorage.

12
00:04:34,797 --> 00:04:36,856
Well, won't it be
kind of cold ?

13
00:04:36,932 --> 00:04:38,866
Well, that's
the point, stupid.

14
00:04:38,934 --> 00:04:41,198
Otherwise, it wouldn't
be an adventure.

15
00:04:41,270 --> 00:04:43,830
And when are you
gonna do this ?

16
00:04:47,076 --> 00:04:49,806
- I don't know.
- [ Exhales ]

17
00:04:49,878 --> 00:04:53,245
After high school.
Before college.

18
00:05:29,151 --> 00:05:31,210
[ Girl Screams ]

19
00:05:32,988 --> 00:05:35,752
[ Grunting, Panting ]

20
00:05:37,526 --> 00:05:40,256
- Marie ! David ?
- I don't know what happened to him.

21
00:05:40,329 --> 00:05:43,696
I don't know what--
I just touched him.

22
00:05:43,766 --> 00:05:45,859
I didn't--
I didn't mean--

23
00:05:45,934 --> 00:05:47,959
- Call an ambulance !
- Don't touch.

24
00:05:48,036 --> 00:05:51,028
- Honey--
-Just get away from me!
- Call an ambulance !

25
00:05:51,106 --> 00:05:53,370
Don't touch me !

26
00:05:53,442 --> 00:05:54,176
- Don't touch me.
-[ Woman ] Ladies and gentlemen,

27
00:05:54,176 --> 00:05:56,610
- Don't touch me.
-[ Woman ] Ladies and gentlemen,

28
00:05:56,678 --> 00:05:59,613
we are now seeing the beginnings
of another stage of human evolution.

29
00:05:59,681 --> 00:06:02,582
These mutations
manifest at puberty...

30
00:06:02,651 --> 00:06:06,712
and are often triggered by periods
of heightened emotional stress.

31
00:06:06,789 --> 00:06:09,485
Thank you, Ms. Grey.
It was quite educational.

32
00:06:09,558 --> 00:06:14,120
However, it fails to address the issue
that is the focus of this hearing.

33
00:06:14,196 --> 00:06:17,825
Three words:
Are mutants dangerous ?

34
00:06:17,900 --> 00:06:20,801
I'm afraid that's
an unfair question, Senator Kelly.

35
00:06:20,869 --> 00:06:23,736
After all, the wrong person behind
the wheel of a car can be dangerous.

36
00:06:23,806 --> 00:06:25,797
Well, we do license
people to drive.

37
00:06:25,874 --> 00:06:29,810
Yes, but not to live.
Senator, it is a fact...

38
00:06:29,878 --> 00:06:33,336
that mutants who have come forward
and revealed themselves publicly...

39
00:06:33,415 --> 00:06:37,112
have been met with fear,
hostility, even violence.

40
00:06:37,186 --> 00:06:39,677
It is because of that
ever-present hostility...

41
00:06:39,755 --> 00:06:43,316
that I am urging the Senate to vote
against mutant registration.

42
00:06:43,392 --> 00:06:47,522
- To force mutants to expose
themselves will only further--
- Expose themselves ?

43
00:06:47,596 --> 00:06:50,190
What is it the mutant community
has to hide I wonder...

44
00:06:50,265 --> 00:06:52,358
that makes them so afraid
to identify themselves ?

45
00:06:52,434 --> 00:06:56,268
- I didn't say they were hiding.
- Let me show you what
is being hidden, Ms. Grey.

46
00:06:56,338 --> 00:07:00,069
I have here a list of names
of identified mutants...

47
00:07:00,142 --> 00:07:02,110
living right here
in the United States.

48
00:07:02,177 --> 00:07:06,511
- Senator Kelly--
- Now, here's a girl in Illinois
who can walk through walls.

49
00:07:06,582 --> 00:07:09,278
Now, what's to stop her
from walking into a bank vault...

50
00:07:09,351 --> 00:07:12,479
or into the White House
or into their houses ?

51
00:07:12,554 --> 00:07:14,784
- Senator Kelly--
- And there are even rumors, Ms. Grey,

52
00:07:14,857 --> 00:07:19,920
of mutants so powerful
that they can enter our minds
and control our thoughts,

53
00:07:19,995 --> 00:07:22,793
taking our
God-given free will.

54
00:07:22,865 --> 00:07:25,993
I think the American people
deserve the right to decide...

55
00:07:26,068 --> 00:07:28,901
whether they want their children
to be in school with mutants,

56
00:07:28,971 --> 00:07:30,836
to be taught by mutants.

57
00:07:32,774 --> 00:07:35,470
Ladies and gentlemen,

58
00:07:35,544 --> 00:07:38,672
the truth is
that mutants are very real,

59
00:07:38,747 --> 00:07:41,682
and they are among us.

60
00:07:41,750 --> 00:07:44,412
- We must know who they are,
-[ Woman ] That's right!

61
00:07:44,486 --> 00:07:46,420
and, above all,
we must know...

62
00:07:46,488 --> 00:07:48,649
what they can do.

63
00:07:50,259 --> 00:07:54,195
[ Applause Continues ]

64
00:08:12,281 --> 00:08:14,215
Eric.

65
00:08:16,785 --> 00:08:20,186
- What are you doing here ?
- Why do you ask questions...

66
00:08:20,255 --> 00:08:22,314
to which you already
know the answers ?

67
00:08:22,391 --> 00:08:25,519
Don't give up
on them, Eric.

68
00:08:25,594 --> 00:08:30,088
What would you have me do, Charles ?
I've heard these arguments before.

69
00:08:30,165 --> 00:08:33,259
It was a long time ago.

70
00:08:33,335 --> 00:08:35,565
Mankind has evolved
since then.

71
00:08:35,637 --> 00:08:37,104
Yes,

72
00:08:37,172 --> 00:08:39,265
into us.

73
00:08:45,581 --> 00:08:47,515
You sneaking around
in here, Charles ?

74
00:08:47,583 --> 00:08:50,177
Whatever are you
looking for?

75
00:08:57,693 --> 00:08:59,684
I'm looking for hope.

76
00:08:59,762 --> 00:09:03,198
I will bring you hope,
old friend.

77
00:09:03,265 --> 00:09:07,099
And I ask
only one thing in return.

78
00:09:09,037 --> 00:09:10,971
Don't get in my way.

79
00:09:13,842 --> 00:09:17,369
We are the future, Charles,
not them.

80
00:09:17,446 --> 00:09:19,539
They no longer matter.

81
00:09:33,529 --> 00:09:35,463
This is it.

82
00:09:42,971 --> 00:09:44,905
Where are we ?

83
00:09:44,973 --> 00:09:47,965
I thought you said you were gonna
take me as far as Laughlin City.

84
00:09:48,043 --> 00:09:49,977
This is Laughlin City.

85
00:09:51,747 --> 00:09:53,681
[ Horn Honking ]

86
00:09:59,555 --> 00:10:02,023
[ People Cheering,
Shouting ]

87
00:10:13,569 --> 00:10:15,594
[ Bell Ringing ]

88
00:10:21,743 --> 00:10:24,303
[ Man ]
Gentlemen, in all my years,

89
00:10:24,379 --> 00:10:26,540
I've never seen
anything like that.

90
00:10:26,615 --> 00:10:28,606
[ Crowd Shouting ]

91
00:10:28,684 --> 00:10:32,745
Are you gonna let this man
walk away with your money ?

92
00:10:32,821 --> 00:10:34,812
- [ Shouting Continues ]
- I'll fight him !

93
00:10:38,861 --> 00:10:43,696
Ladies and gentlemen,
our savior !

94
00:10:45,133 --> 00:10:47,192
Whatever you do,
don't hit him in the balls.

95
00:10:47,269 --> 00:10:51,228
- You said anything goes.
- Anything goes,
but he'll take it personal.

96
00:10:51,306 --> 00:10:53,900
[ Bell Rings ]

97
00:11:16,064 --> 00:11:20,000
-[ Bell Rings ]
- Ladies and gentlemen,

98
00:11:20,068 --> 00:11:24,027
tonight's winner
and still king of the cage,

99
00:11:24,106 --> 00:11:26,074
the Wolverine!

100
00:11:26,141 --> 00:11:30,077
[ Cheering, Booing ]

101
00:11:54,469 --> 00:11:56,562
You want
something new, honey ?

102
00:11:58,006 --> 00:12:00,736
Or are you sticking
with water ?

103
00:12:09,618 --> 00:12:11,552
I'll have a beer.

104
00:12:21,129 --> 00:12:25,566
[ Man ] Ellis Island,
once the arrival point
for thousands of American immigrants...

105
00:12:25,634 --> 00:12:27,568
is opening
its doors again.

106
00:12:27,636 --> 00:12:31,572
Preparations are nearly
completed for the upcoming
United Nations world summit.

107
00:12:31,640 --> 00:12:33,665
With nearly
every invitation confirmed,

108
00:12:33,742 --> 00:12:38,907
the event promises to be
the largest single gathering
of world leaders in history.

109
00:12:38,981 --> 00:12:43,543
The leaders of over 200 nations
will discuss issues ranging from
the world's economic climate...

110
00:12:43,618 --> 00:12:48,282
and weapons treaties
to the mutant phenomenon and
its impact on our world stage.

111
00:12:48,357 --> 00:12:51,383
Many American legislators
have contended...

112
00:12:51,460 --> 00:12:55,590
that debate over mutant issues
should be the primary focus
of what is, on the surface,

113
00:12:55,664 --> 00:12:58,656
a strictly
diplomatic affair.

114
00:12:58,734 --> 00:13:01,703
- You owe me some money.
- Come on, Stu. Let's not do this.

115
00:13:01,770 --> 00:13:06,207
No man takes a beating like that
without a mark to show for it.

116
00:13:06,274 --> 00:13:08,868
Come on, buddy.
This isn't gonna be worth it.

117
00:13:08,944 --> 00:13:11,970
- I know what you are.
- You lost your money. Keep this up,
you'll lose something else.

118
00:13:12,047 --> 00:13:13,639
Come on, buddy.

119
00:13:15,717 --> 00:13:16,945
Look out !

120
00:13:30,365 --> 00:13:32,629
Get out of my bar,
freak.

121
00:13:43,779 --> 00:13:45,713
[ Growls ]

122
00:14:48,543 --> 00:14:50,465
[ Thud ]

123
00:15:21,563 --> 00:15:25,522
- What the hell are you doing ?
- I'm sorry. I needed a ride.

124
00:15:25,600 --> 00:15:28,091
- Thought you might help me.
- Get out.

125
00:15:29,538 --> 00:15:32,200
- Where am I supposed to go ?
- I don't know.

126
00:15:32,274 --> 00:15:34,799
- You don't know or you don't care ?
- Pick one.

127
00:15:38,880 --> 00:15:41,906
- I saved your life.
- No, you didn't.

128
00:15:57,165 --> 00:15:59,633
You don't have anything
to eat, do you ?

129
00:16:20,822 --> 00:16:22,756
I'm Rogue.

130
00:16:28,396 --> 00:16:30,660
Were you in the army?

131
00:16:30,732 --> 00:16:33,166
Doesn't that mean
you were in the army ?

132
00:16:40,442 --> 00:16:42,376
- Wow.
- What ?

133
00:16:46,181 --> 00:16:49,014
- Suddenly my life
doesn't look that bad.
- If you'd prefer the road--

134
00:16:49,084 --> 00:16:52,520
No. No. It looks great.

135
00:16:55,490 --> 00:16:58,323
Looks cozy.

136
00:17:04,699 --> 00:17:07,031
Put your hands
on the heater.

137
00:17:08,203 --> 00:17:10,569
I'm not gonna
hurt you, kid.

138
00:17:10,639 --> 00:17:13,369
It's nothing personal.
It's just that...

139
00:17:13,441 --> 00:17:15,568
when people touch my skin,
something happens.

140
00:17:15,644 --> 00:17:19,375
- What ?
- I don't know.

141
00:17:19,447 --> 00:17:21,813
They just get hurt.

142
00:17:21,883 --> 00:17:23,817
Fair enough.

143
00:17:27,956 --> 00:17:31,414
When they come out,
does it hurt ?

144
00:17:34,462 --> 00:17:36,396
Every time.

145
00:17:39,501 --> 00:17:42,265
So, what kind of a name
is Rogue ?

146
00:17:44,406 --> 00:17:47,773
I don't know. What kind
of a name is Wolverine ?

147
00:17:51,846 --> 00:17:53,780
My name's Logan.

148
00:17:55,784 --> 00:17:57,718
Marie.

149
00:17:59,821 --> 00:18:02,722
You know, you should wear
your seat belt.

150
00:18:02,791 --> 00:18:04,952
Look, kid. I don't need advice
on auto safety from--

151
00:18:49,638 --> 00:18:51,629
[ Grunting, Sobbing ]

152
00:19:00,715 --> 00:19:02,649
[ Bones Cracking ]

153
00:19:10,859 --> 00:19:13,623
You all right ?

154
00:19:13,695 --> 00:19:15,629
- Kid, are you all right ?
- I'm stuck !

155
00:19:23,171 --> 00:19:25,469
[ Sniffing ]

156
00:20:47,998 --> 00:20:50,432
[ Hissing ]

157
00:20:58,676 --> 00:21:01,440
[ Hissing Continues ]

158
00:21:01,512 --> 00:21:06,506
- Weren't you supposed
to bring someone back with you ?
- [ Growls ]

159
00:21:18,095 --> 00:21:20,290
- What happened ?
- They knew.

160
00:21:29,139 --> 00:21:31,073
Charles.

161
00:21:39,750 --> 00:21:41,684
Hmm.

162
00:21:43,821 --> 00:21:46,289
- Where is the mutant now ?
- With them.

163
00:21:49,059 --> 00:21:51,619
I have made the first move.

164
00:21:52,796 --> 00:21:55,560
That is all
they know.

165
00:21:55,633 --> 00:21:58,500
Come. The U.N. summit
is approaching.

166
00:21:58,569 --> 00:22:00,662
Time for
our little test.

167
00:23:11,375 --> 00:23:13,309
[ Man's Voice ]
Where's he going ?

168
00:23:40,304 --> 00:23:42,864
Where are you going ?

169
00:23:48,645 --> 00:23:50,579
[ Whispering ]
Over here.

170
00:24:18,175 --> 00:24:20,109
Where are you going ?
[ Whispering ] This way.

171
00:24:20,177 --> 00:24:22,111
He's over there.

172
00:24:29,086 --> 00:24:31,418
-[ Boy #1 ] Let's go.
-[ Boy #2 ] What's your hurry?

173
00:24:47,004 --> 00:24:48,938
[ Door Opens ]

174
00:24:55,646 --> 00:24:58,672
Good morning, Logan.

175
00:24:58,749 --> 00:25:01,547
I'd like your definitions of weak
and strong anthropic principles...

176
00:25:01,618 --> 00:25:03,609
on my desk
on Wednesday.

177
00:25:03,687 --> 00:25:05,621
That'll be all.

178
00:25:12,062 --> 00:25:14,326
- Bye, Professor.
- Bye, Kitty.

179
00:25:18,235 --> 00:25:20,169
Physics.

180
00:25:21,538 --> 00:25:23,768
I'm Charles Xavier.
Would you like some breakfast ?

181
00:25:23,841 --> 00:25:28,107
- Where am I ?
- Westchester, New York.

182
00:25:28,178 --> 00:25:32,342
You were attacked. My people
brought you here for medical attention.

183
00:25:32,416 --> 00:25:35,613
- I don't need medical attention.
- Yes, of course.

184
00:25:38,121 --> 00:25:40,681
- Where's the girl ?
- Rogue ? She's here. She's fine.

185
00:25:40,757 --> 00:25:43,453
Really.

186
00:25:43,527 --> 00:25:49,397
Ah, Logan, I'd like you to meet
Ororo Monroe, also called Storm.

187
00:25:49,466 --> 00:25:52,629
- This is Scott Summers,
also called Cyclops.
- Hello.

188
00:25:55,639 --> 00:25:58,665
They saved your life.

189
00:25:58,742 --> 00:26:01,472
I believe you've already
met Dr.Jean Grey.

190
00:26:03,046 --> 00:26:05,674
You're in my school for the gifted.
For mutants.

191
00:26:05,749 --> 00:26:09,241
- You'll be safe here from Magneto.
- What's a Magneto ?

192
00:26:09,319 --> 00:26:12,982
A very powerful mutant
who believes that a war is brewing...

193
00:26:13,056 --> 00:26:15,889
between mutants and
the rest of humanity.

194
00:26:15,959 --> 00:26:17,893
I've been following
his activities for some time.

195
00:26:17,961 --> 00:26:20,759
The man who attacked you is an associate
of his called Sabretooth.

196
00:26:20,831 --> 00:26:22,822
Sabretooth ?

197
00:26:24,635 --> 00:26:27,570
Storm.
[ Clicks Tongue ]

198
00:26:27,638 --> 00:26:30,266
What do they call you ?
Wheels ?

199
00:26:31,475 --> 00:26:34,273
This is the stupidest
thing I've ever heard.

200
00:26:37,748 --> 00:26:42,048
Cyclops, right ?
You wanna get out of my way ?

201
00:26:43,921 --> 00:26:47,639
Logan, it's been almost
1 5 years, hasn't it ?

202
00:26:47,773 --> 00:26:51,470
Living from day to day,
moving from place to place,

203
00:26:51,543 --> 00:26:54,637
with no memory
of who or what you are.

204
00:26:54,713 --> 00:26:56,647
Shut up.

205
00:26:56,715 --> 00:26:58,740
Give me a chance.

206
00:26:58,817 --> 00:27:02,253
I may be able to help you
find some answers.

207
00:27:02,321 --> 00:27:04,687
How do you know ?

208
00:27:04,756 --> 00:27:06,951
[ Xavier's Voice ]
You're not the only one with gifts.

209
00:27:07,025 --> 00:27:08,959
- Where are you going ?
-[ Cyclops' Voice ] Where's he going ?

210
00:27:09,027 --> 00:27:11,552
[ Xavier's Voice ]
What are you doing there ?

211
00:27:15,667 --> 00:27:17,294
What is this place ?

212
00:27:19,338 --> 00:27:22,273
[ Xavier ]
Anonymity is a mutant's first chance...

213
00:27:22,341 --> 00:27:24,275
against
the world's hostility.

214
00:27:24,343 --> 00:27:27,244
[ Boy ]
Hey, no powers!

215
00:27:27,312 --> 00:27:30,145
To the public, we're merely
a school for gifted youngsters.

216
00:27:31,516 --> 00:27:35,179
Cyclops, Storm andJean
were some of my first students.

217
00:27:35,254 --> 00:27:39,520
I protected them, taught them
to control their powers...

218
00:27:39,591 --> 00:27:43,857
and in time,
teach others to do the same.

219
00:27:43,929 --> 00:27:45,954
The students
are mostly runaways.

220
00:27:46,031 --> 00:27:48,056
Frightened, alone.

221
00:27:48,133 --> 00:27:50,761
Some with gifts so extreme
that they've become a danger...

222
00:27:50,836 --> 00:27:53,100
to themselves
and those around them.

223
00:27:53,171 --> 00:27:55,662
Like your friend, Rogue.

224
00:27:55,741 --> 00:27:58,733
Incapable of physical human contact,
probably for the rest of her life,

225
00:27:58,810 --> 00:28:02,507
and yet here she is
with others her own age,

226
00:28:02,581 --> 00:28:06,039
learning being accepted,
not feared.

227
00:28:17,262 --> 00:28:19,253
-John.
- Sorry.

228
00:28:24,536 --> 00:28:26,970
I'm Bobby.
What's your name ?

229
00:28:27,039 --> 00:28:30,497
- Rogue.
-[ Logan's Voice ]
What'll happen to her?

230
00:28:30,575 --> 00:28:34,511
[ Xavier ] Well, that's
up to her. Rejoin the world
as an educated young woman...

231
00:28:34,579 --> 00:28:36,513
or stay on
to teach others...

232
00:28:36,581 --> 00:28:39,448
to become what the children
have affectionately called X-Men.

233
00:28:39,518 --> 00:28:42,544
Welcome to Mutant High.

234
00:28:43,922 --> 00:28:46,390
[ Xavier ]
But the school is merely a public face.

235
00:28:46,458 --> 00:28:50,451
The lower levels, however, are
an entirely different matter.

236
00:28:55,701 --> 00:29:00,400
When I was a boy, I discovered I had
the power to control people's minds,

237
00:29:00,472 --> 00:29:03,407
make them think or do
whatever I wanted.

238
00:29:03,475 --> 00:29:07,639
When I was 1 7,
I met a young man named Eric Lensherr.

239
00:29:07,713 --> 00:29:09,943
He, too, had
an unusual power.

240
00:29:10,015 --> 00:29:14,042
He could create magnetic fields
and control metal.

241
00:29:14,119 --> 00:29:16,280
Believing that humanity
would never accept us,

242
00:29:16,355 --> 00:29:19,552
he grew angry and vengeful.

243
00:29:20,892 --> 00:29:22,826
He became Magneto.

244
00:29:24,463 --> 00:29:28,126
There are mutants out there
with incredible powers, Logan,

245
00:29:28,200 --> 00:29:31,863
and many who do not share
my respect for mankind.

246
00:29:31,937 --> 00:29:36,374
If no one is equipped to oppose them,
humanity's days could be over.

247
00:29:36,441 --> 00:29:38,602
I'll make a deal
with you, Logan.

248
00:29:38,677 --> 00:29:42,670
Give me 48 hours to find out
what Magneto wants with you,

249
00:29:42,748 --> 00:29:45,911
and I give you my word
that I will use all my power...

250
00:29:45,984 --> 00:29:48,680
to help you piece together
what you've lost...

251
00:29:48,754 --> 00:29:49,187
and what
you're looking for.

252
00:29:49,187 --> 00:29:51,212
and what
you're looking for.

253
00:29:53,225 --> 00:29:53,859
[ Crowd Cheering, Shouting ]

254
00:29:53,859 --> 00:29:55,349
[ Crowd Cheering, Shouting ]

255
00:30:19,050 --> 00:30:22,110
[ Kelly ] Senator, listen,
you favor gun registration,yes ?

256
00:30:22,187 --> 00:30:24,212
Well, some of these
so-called children...

257
00:30:24,289 --> 00:30:28,817
possess more than ten times
the destructive force of any handgun.

258
00:30:28,894 --> 00:30:32,625
No, I don't see a difference.
All I see are weapons in our schools.

259
00:30:32,697 --> 00:30:35,564
Well, that's fair enough.
All right.

260
00:30:35,634 --> 00:30:37,795
So ?

261
00:30:37,869 --> 00:30:42,101
It's gonna be close.
A vote this loaded is always close.

262
00:30:42,174 --> 00:30:45,405
What about the U.N. summit ?
The whole world will be watching.

263
00:30:45,477 --> 00:30:47,968
Maybe there's some way
you could use that to your advantage.

264
00:30:48,046 --> 00:30:49,980
We're Americans, Henry.

265
00:30:50,048 --> 00:30:52,744
Let the rest of the damn world deal
with mutants in their own way.

266
00:30:52,818 --> 00:30:55,252
You know this situation ?

267
00:30:55,320 --> 00:30:57,811
These mutants ?

268
00:30:57,889 --> 00:30:59,948
People like this Jean Grey ?

269
00:31:01,526 --> 00:31:04,757
If it were up to me,
I'd lock 'em all away.

270
00:31:04,830 --> 00:31:10,200
It's a war.
It's the reason people like me exist.

271
00:31:17,976 --> 00:31:20,467
Where the hell are we ?

272
00:31:30,155 --> 00:31:32,350
Pilot !

273
00:31:35,093 --> 00:31:38,551
People like you are the reason
I was afraid to go to school as a child.

274
00:32:11,229 --> 00:32:14,858
- I'm sorry.
- For what ?

275
00:32:14,933 --> 00:32:17,197
If I hurt you.

276
00:32:26,611 --> 00:32:30,672
So, couldn't wait to get
my shirt off again, huh ?

277
00:32:47,561 --> 00:32:50,189
[Jean ]
The metal is an alloy called adamantium.

278
00:32:50,264 --> 00:32:55,998
Supposedly indestructible.
It's been surgically grafted
to his entire skeleton.

279
00:32:56,069 --> 00:32:59,436
How could he have survived
a procedure like that ?

280
00:32:59,506 --> 00:33:03,408
His mutation. He has uncharted
regenerative capability,

281
00:33:03,477 --> 00:33:06,378
which enables him
to heal rapidly.

282
00:33:06,446 --> 00:33:10,280
This also makes his age
impossible to determine.

283
00:33:10,350 --> 00:33:12,978
He could very well
be older than you, Professor.

284
00:33:14,321 --> 00:33:17,154
- [ Cyclops ] Who did this to him ?
- He doesn't know.

285
00:33:17,224 --> 00:33:20,785
Nor does he remember anything
about his life before it happened.

286
00:33:20,861 --> 00:33:23,489
Experimentation
on mutants.

287
00:33:23,564 --> 00:33:25,623
[ Sighs ]
It's not unheard of.

288
00:33:25,699 --> 00:33:28,930
But I've never seen
anything like this before.

289
00:33:29,002 --> 00:33:31,937
[ Cyclops ] What do you think
Magneto wants with him ?

290
00:33:32,005 --> 00:33:35,813
I'm not entirely sure
it's him Magneto wants.

291
00:33:47,625 --> 00:33:50,685
[ Bird Cooing ]

292
00:33:57,535 --> 00:33:59,469
Yech !

293
00:33:59,537 --> 00:34:02,097
[ Magneto ]
Toad has a wicked tongue, Senator.

294
00:34:02,173 --> 00:34:04,607
Just like you.

295
00:34:11,783 --> 00:34:14,149
Who are you people ?
Where's Henry ?

296
00:34:14,218 --> 00:34:17,813
Mr. Guyrich has been dead
for some time, Senator.

297
00:34:17,889 --> 00:34:20,722
But I've had Mystique here
keep you company.

298
00:34:20,792 --> 00:34:22,726
She takes
so many shapes.

299
00:34:22,794 --> 00:34:26,389
Whatever you do to me,
you'll make me right.

300
00:34:26,464 --> 00:34:30,332
Every word I've spoken
will be confirmed.

301
00:34:33,271 --> 00:34:35,637
Are you a God-fearing
man, Senator ?

302
00:34:35,706 --> 00:34:38,732
That's such
a strange phrase.

303
00:34:38,810 --> 00:34:41,574
I've always thought
of God as a teacher,

304
00:34:41,646 --> 00:34:45,138
as a bringer of light,
wisdom and understanding.

305
00:34:45,216 --> 00:34:50,950
You see, I think
what you really are afraid of is me.

306
00:34:51,022 --> 00:34:54,150
Me and my kind.
The Brotherhood of Mutants.

307
00:34:56,594 --> 00:34:59,028
Though it's not
so surprising, really.

308
00:34:59,096 --> 00:35:03,624
Mankind has always feared
what it doesn't understand.

309
00:35:05,269 --> 00:35:08,295
Well, don't fear God,
Senator,

310
00:35:08,372 --> 00:35:10,306
and certainly,
don't fear me.

311
00:35:11,442 --> 00:35:13,376
Not anymore.

312
00:35:15,513 --> 00:35:17,504
What do you intend
to do to me ?

313
00:35:17,582 --> 00:35:21,018
Let's just say
God works too slowly.

314
00:36:36,594 --> 00:36:38,858
I think you'll
be comfortable here.

315
00:36:38,930 --> 00:36:42,127
- Where is your room ?
- With Scott down the hall.

316
00:36:43,601 --> 00:36:46,968
Is that your gift ?
Putting up with that guy ?

317
00:36:47,038 --> 00:36:50,701
Actually, I'm telekinetic.
I can move things with my mind.

318
00:36:50,775 --> 00:36:52,902
Really ?
What kinds of things ?

319
00:36:54,478 --> 00:36:57,276
All kinds of things.

320
00:36:57,348 --> 00:37:00,146
I also have some
telepathic ability.

321
00:37:00,217 --> 00:37:03,653
- What, like your Professor ?
- Nowhere near that powerful.

322
00:37:03,721 --> 00:37:06,554
But he's teaching me
to develop it.

323
00:37:06,624 --> 00:37:08,558
I'm sure he is.

324
00:37:10,628 --> 00:37:12,892
- So read my mind.
- I'd rather not.

325
00:37:12,964 --> 00:37:15,455
Come on.
You afraid you might like it ?

326
00:37:15,533 --> 00:37:17,433
I doubt it.

327
00:37:38,489 --> 00:37:40,081
What do you see ?

328
00:37:41,726 --> 00:37:43,990
Scott.

329
00:37:46,931 --> 00:37:49,195
Good night, Logan.

330
00:37:58,109 --> 00:38:00,043
You gonna tell me
to stay away from your girl ?

331
00:38:00,111 --> 00:38:02,375
If I had to do that,
she wouldn't be my girl.

332
00:38:02,446 --> 00:38:06,041
Hmm. Well, then, I guess
you've got nothing to worry about,

333
00:38:06,117 --> 00:38:08,051
do you, Cyclops ?

334
00:38:08,119 --> 00:38:12,488
Yeah, it must just burn you up that
a boy like me saved your life, huh ?

335
00:38:12,556 --> 00:38:15,047
You ought to be careful.
I might not be there next time.

336
00:38:15,126 --> 00:38:18,220
Oh, and, Logan,

337
00:38:18,295 --> 00:38:19,296
stay away from my girl.

338
00:38:19,296 --> 00:38:20,888
stay away from my girl.

339
00:38:35,312 --> 00:38:37,246
[ Grunts ]

340
00:38:39,116 --> 00:38:41,050
[ Door Opens ]

341
00:38:46,957 --> 00:38:49,391
[ Mumbling ]

342
00:38:54,265 --> 00:38:56,597
Logan.

343
00:39:05,676 --> 00:39:08,839
Logan. Logan, wake up.

344
00:39:25,529 --> 00:39:28,521
- [ Gasps, Yells ]
- [ Screams ]

345
00:39:40,878 --> 00:39:44,143
- [ Gasping ]
- Help me.

346
00:39:47,017 --> 00:39:49,986
Somebody help !

347
00:40:20,692 --> 00:40:22,922
Scott, grab a pillow.

348
00:40:25,163 --> 00:40:27,893
It was an accident.

349
00:40:36,842 --> 00:40:40,141
-[ Xavier ] Logan ?
- What happened ?

350
00:40:41,480 --> 00:40:44,074
- Is she all right ?
- She'll be all right.

351
00:40:46,251 --> 00:40:48,185
What did she do to me ?

352
00:40:48,253 --> 00:40:52,087
Whenever Rogue touches someone, she
takes their energy, their life force.

353
00:40:52,157 --> 00:40:56,093
In the case of mutants, she absorbs
their gifts for a short while.

354
00:40:56,161 --> 00:40:58,652
In your case,
your ability to heal.

355
00:41:01,032 --> 00:41:03,023
I feel like
she almost killed me.

356
00:41:03,101 --> 00:41:06,264
If she'd held out any longer,
she could have.

357
00:41:17,616 --> 00:41:19,550
[ Door Opens ]

358
00:42:01,793 --> 00:42:04,990
How are we feeling, Senator ?
Advanced, I hope.

359
00:42:06,898 --> 00:42:08,832
Hmm.

360
00:42:22,614 --> 00:42:25,048
What the hell
have you done to me ?

361
00:42:25,116 --> 00:42:29,143
Senator, this is pointless.
Where would you go ?

362
00:42:29,220 --> 00:42:31,848
Who would take you in
now that you're one of us ?

363
00:42:41,533 --> 00:42:44,058
[ Yells ]

364
00:43:15,467 --> 00:43:17,264
[ Growls ]

365
00:43:28,513 --> 00:43:32,950
Tommy, let it go!
Tommy, please let it go!

366
00:43:33,018 --> 00:43:34,952
I'm telling Mommy.

367
00:43:49,367 --> 00:43:52,029
[ Boy ]
Is that a mutant ?

368
00:43:57,142 --> 00:43:59,076
[ Woman On TV]
...of this week's U.N. summit.

369
00:43:59,144 --> 00:44:01,612
With the leaders
of over 200 nations attending,

370
00:44:01,680 --> 00:44:04,649
the secret service
has transformed Ellis Island...

371
00:44:04,716 --> 00:44:08,152
into a veritable Fort Knox
for tomorrow night's opening gala.

372
00:44:08,219 --> 00:44:11,916
Ellis Island rests less than one mile
from the shores of Manhattan.

373
00:44:13,425 --> 00:44:15,359
[ Bobby ]
Rogue.

374
00:44:15,427 --> 00:44:19,295
- Bobby.
- Rogue, what did you do ?

375
00:44:20,665 --> 00:44:22,724
They say that you're
stealing other mutants' powers.

376
00:44:22,801 --> 00:44:24,792
No, no.
I borrowed his powers.

377
00:44:24,869 --> 00:44:28,168
You never use your power
against another mutant.

378
00:44:30,241 --> 00:44:32,709
I had no choice.

379
00:44:32,777 --> 00:44:34,870
- No, you have to understand me.
- If I were you,

380
00:44:34,946 --> 00:44:37,380
I'd get myself out of here.

381
00:44:39,784 --> 00:44:43,686
- What do you mean ?
- Listen, the students are freaked.

382
00:44:43,755 --> 00:44:46,724
Professor Xavier's furious.
I don't know what he'll do with you.

383
00:44:50,328 --> 00:44:52,990
I think it'll be easier
on your own.

384
00:44:58,970 --> 00:45:01,200
You should go.

385
00:45:24,462 --> 00:45:26,430
[ Xavier ]
What are you looking for, Eric ?

386
00:45:26,498 --> 00:45:31,367
It's strange. There are
more powerful mutants out there.

387
00:45:31,436 --> 00:45:33,631
Why should this one
be so important to him ?

388
00:45:33,705 --> 00:45:36,071
- Maybe it's his way with people.
- You don't like him.

389
00:45:37,509 --> 00:45:41,104
- How could you tell ?
- Well, I am psychic, you know.

390
00:45:42,514 --> 00:45:44,448
- Where is she ?
- Who ?

391
00:45:44,516 --> 00:45:46,450
Rogue.

392
00:45:46,518 --> 00:45:48,543
She's gone.

393
00:45:53,024 --> 00:45:55,618
[ Woman's Voice ]
Welcome, Professor.

394
00:45:58,463 --> 00:46:00,727
Welcome to Cerebro.

395
00:46:05,303 --> 00:46:08,932
This certainly is
a big, round room.

396
00:46:09,007 --> 00:46:12,602
The brain waves of mutants
are different from average human beings.

397
00:46:12,677 --> 00:46:14,611
This device amplifies
my power,

398
00:46:14,679 --> 00:46:17,443
allowing me to locate mutants
across great distances.

399
00:46:17,515 --> 00:46:20,450
That's how I intend
to find Rogue.

400
00:46:20,518 --> 00:46:23,487
- Why don't you just use it
to find Magneto ?
- I've been trying.

401
00:46:23,555 --> 00:46:27,286
But he seems to have found
some way to shield himself from it.

402
00:46:27,358 --> 00:46:30,555
How would he know
how to do that ?

403
00:46:30,628 --> 00:46:33,688
Because he
helped me build it.

404
00:46:33,765 --> 00:46:36,290
Now, if you'll excuse me.

405
00:46:48,413 --> 00:46:50,813
Have you ever--

406
00:46:50,882 --> 00:46:53,112
Used Cerebro ?

407
00:46:53,184 --> 00:46:56,711
No. It takes
a degree of control,

408
00:46:56,788 --> 00:47:00,451
and, uh,
for someone like me, it's--

409
00:47:00,525 --> 00:47:02,424
Dangerous.

410
00:47:05,327 --> 00:47:08,694
[ Telepathic Voices
Low, Distinct ]

411
00:47:39,928 --> 00:47:43,125
[ Man Over P.A.]
...now boarding on track four.

412
00:47:46,802 --> 00:47:49,464
- She's at the train station.
-[ Logan ] Where is it ?

413
00:47:49,538 --> 00:47:52,837
A few miles west of here.
Logan,you can't leave the mansion.

414
00:47:52,908 --> 00:47:57,174
- It's just the opportunity
Magneto needs.
- I'm the reason she took off.

415
00:47:57,246 --> 00:48:01,410
- We had a deal.
- She's all right. She's just upset.

416
00:48:01,483 --> 00:48:03,747
Storm, Cyclops, find her.
See if you can talk to her.

417
00:48:13,962 --> 00:48:17,398
- What ?
- Where's my motorcycle ?

418
00:48:54,136 --> 00:48:56,297
[ Logan ]
Hey, kid.

419
00:49:11,019 --> 00:49:12,953
I'm sorry
about last night.

420
00:49:14,456 --> 00:49:16,390
Me too.

421
00:49:18,327 --> 00:49:23,731
- You running again ?
- I heard the professor was mad at me.

422
00:49:23,799 --> 00:49:27,997
- Well, who told you that ?
- A boy at school.

423
00:49:28,070 --> 00:49:31,471
- When's the last time you saw her ?
- She was supposed to meet me for lunch.

424
00:49:37,212 --> 00:49:40,181
You look around.
I'll check with the ticket agent.

425
00:49:53,662 --> 00:49:55,596
Welcome, Professor.

426
00:50:20,555 --> 00:50:24,821
- You think I should go back.
- No, I think you should
follow your instincts.

427
00:50:30,766 --> 00:50:33,394
The first boy I ever kissed...

428
00:50:33,468 --> 00:50:36,995
ended up in a coma
for three weeks.

429
00:50:39,241 --> 00:50:41,801
I can still feel him
inside my head.

430
00:50:44,212 --> 00:50:46,544
And it's the same
with you.

431
00:51:13,208 --> 00:51:17,577
There's not many people that'll
understand what you're going through,

432
00:51:17,646 --> 00:51:21,844
but I think this guy's
Xavier's one of them.

433
00:51:21,917 --> 00:51:25,216
He seems to genuinely
wanna help you,

434
00:51:25,287 --> 00:51:27,585
and that's
a rare thing...

435
00:51:29,157 --> 00:51:31,421
for people like us.

436
00:51:37,099 --> 00:51:40,091
[ Train Rumbles ]

437
00:51:42,571 --> 00:51:45,233
So, what do you say ?

438
00:51:45,307 --> 00:51:48,572
Give these geeks
one more shot ?

439
00:51:50,145 --> 00:51:52,079
Come on.
I'll take care of you.

440
00:51:54,716 --> 00:51:57,708
- You promise ?
- Yeah.

441
00:51:57,786 --> 00:51:59,720
Yeah, I promise.

442
00:52:13,001 --> 00:52:14,935
Come along now.

443
00:52:16,838 --> 00:52:20,239
She's about 1 7.
Uh, my height.

444
00:52:20,308 --> 00:52:23,471
Has brown hair,
and she--

445
00:52:23,545 --> 00:52:25,410
[ Growls ]

446
00:52:29,818 --> 00:52:32,844
[ Growls ]
Scream for me.

447
00:52:32,921 --> 00:52:35,185
[ Gasping ]

448
00:52:58,869 --> 00:53:01,030
[ Roars ]

449
00:53:17,888 --> 00:53:20,721
- Quit playing around.
- [ Growls ]

450
00:53:20,791 --> 00:53:22,452
[ Rumbling ]

451
00:53:26,297 --> 00:53:28,288
[ Woman Screaming ]

452
00:53:28,366 --> 00:53:30,857
[ Electricity Zapping ]

453
00:54:02,233 --> 00:54:04,497
You must be Wolverine.

454
00:54:06,270 --> 00:54:09,899
That remarkable metal doesn't run
through your entire body, does it ?

455
00:54:22,420 --> 00:54:25,446
Stop ! Stop it !

456
00:54:25,523 --> 00:54:28,424
What the hell
do you want with me ?

457
00:54:28,492 --> 00:54:32,724
You ? My dear boy,
whoever said I wanted you ?

458
00:54:54,318 --> 00:54:56,252
Young people.

459
00:55:00,291 --> 00:55:02,384
[ Sirens Wailing ]

460
00:55:07,965 --> 00:55:10,160
[ Man ] All right, hold it.
Hold it right there.

461
00:55:10,234 --> 00:55:13,294
Stay where you are.
Put your hands over your heads now.

462
00:55:45,870 --> 00:55:49,328
You Homo sapiens
and your guns.

463
00:55:53,177 --> 00:55:55,645
- That's enough, Eric.
- Let them go.

464
00:56:01,118 --> 00:56:04,246
Why not come out where
I can see you, Charles ?

465
00:56:07,391 --> 00:56:09,325
- What do you--
- Want her for ?

466
00:56:10,361 --> 00:56:13,296
Can't you read my mind ?

467
00:56:14,798 --> 00:56:18,461
What now ?
Save the girl ?

468
00:56:18,536 --> 00:56:23,064
You'll have to kill me, Charles.
And what will that accomplish ?

469
00:56:23,140 --> 00:56:27,042
Let them pass that law. They'll
have you in chains with a number
burned into your forehead.

470
00:56:27,111 --> 00:56:29,306
- It won't be--
- That way.

471
00:56:29,380 --> 00:56:31,541
Then kill me
and find out.

472
00:56:34,251 --> 00:56:37,311
Huh ? Then release me.

473
00:56:45,563 --> 00:56:47,497
Fine.

474
00:56:53,804 --> 00:56:55,897
-[ Gunshot ]
- [ Crowd Gasping, Screaming ]

475
00:57:00,477 --> 00:57:02,843
Care to press your luck,
Charles ?

476
00:57:02,913 --> 00:57:05,711
[ Guns Cocking ]

477
00:57:07,418 --> 00:57:11,081
- I don't think I can stop them all.
- [ Grunting ]

478
00:57:25,469 --> 00:57:27,460
Still unwilling
to make sacrifices.

479
00:57:27,538 --> 00:57:30,632
That's what
makes you weak.

480
00:57:42,386 --> 00:57:44,946
Good-bye, Charles.

481
00:58:14,961 --> 00:58:18,419
- You said he wanted me.
- I made a terrible mistake.

482
00:58:18,498 --> 00:58:21,990
His helmet was somehow designed
to block my telepathy.

483
00:58:23,570 --> 00:58:26,937
I couldn't see what
he was after till it was too late.

484
00:58:27,006 --> 00:58:29,133
- Where are you going ?
- I'm gonna find her.

485
00:58:29,209 --> 00:58:32,337
- How ?
- The traditional way. Look.

486
00:58:35,682 --> 00:58:38,173
Logan, you can't
do this alone.

487
00:58:38,251 --> 00:58:41,243
Who's gonna help me ? You ?
So far you've all done a bang-up job.

488
00:58:41,321 --> 00:58:43,585
Then help us.
Fight with us.

489
00:58:43,656 --> 00:58:46,386
Fight with you ?
What,join the team ? Be an X-Man ?

490
00:58:46,459 --> 00:58:49,223
Who the hell do you think you are ?
You're a mutant.

491
00:58:49,295 --> 00:58:52,355
The whole world out there is full
of people that hate and fear you.

492
00:58:52,432 --> 00:58:56,163
And you're wasting your time
trying to protect 'em ?
I got better things to do.

493
00:58:56,236 --> 00:59:00,696
You know, Magneto's right.
There's a war coming.

494
00:59:00,774 --> 00:59:05,006
- You sure you're on the right side ?
- At least I've chosen a side.

495
00:59:12,752 --> 00:59:16,381
I'm looking
for Dr.Jean Grey.

496
00:59:25,031 --> 00:59:27,465
Senator Kelly.

497
00:59:27,534 --> 00:59:29,900
I'm Professor
Charles Xavier.

498
00:59:31,805 --> 00:59:35,969
I was afraid if I went
to a hospital, they would--

499
00:59:36,042 --> 00:59:38,067
Treat you like a mutant ?

500
00:59:40,146 --> 00:59:44,082
We're not what you think.
Not all of us.

501
00:59:44,150 --> 00:59:47,984
Tell it to the ones
who did this to me.

502
00:59:52,425 --> 00:59:54,359
Senator...

503
00:59:59,065 --> 01:00:02,523
I want you to try and relax.

504
01:00:05,505 --> 01:00:07,439
I'm not going
to hurt you.

505
01:00:59,692 --> 01:01:02,786
Welcome to the future,

506
01:01:02,862 --> 01:01:04,796
brother.

507
01:01:10,904 --> 01:01:15,068
The machine emits radiation
that triggers mutation
in ordinary human beings.

508
01:01:15,141 --> 01:01:17,234
But the mutation
is unnatural.

509
01:01:17,310 --> 01:01:19,938
Kelly's body is rejecting it.
His cells began...

510
01:01:20,013 --> 01:01:22,345
to break down
almost immediately.

511
01:01:22,415 --> 01:01:25,316
- What effect does radiation
have on mutants ?
- There appears to be none.

512
01:01:25,385 --> 01:01:29,219
But I fear it will seriously
harm any normal person exposed to it.

513
01:01:29,289 --> 01:01:33,191
- So what does Magneto want with Rogue ?
- I don't know.

514
01:01:35,361 --> 01:01:37,829
[ Cyclops ]
Wait a second.

515
01:01:37,897 --> 01:01:40,661
You said this machine
draws its power from Magneto...

516
01:01:40,733 --> 01:01:43,531
-and that it weakened him.
-[ Xavier ] Yes.

517
01:01:44,837 --> 01:01:46,930
In fact,
it nearly killed him.

518
01:01:47,006 --> 01:01:49,668
He's gonna transfer
his power to Rogue...

519
01:01:49,742 --> 01:01:52,939
and use her
to power the machine.

520
01:01:55,581 --> 01:01:57,742
Is somebody there ?

521
01:01:59,585 --> 01:02:02,577
Yes. I'm here.

522
01:02:04,524 --> 01:02:07,516
Please don't leave me.

523
01:02:08,728 --> 01:02:11,128
Don't want to be alone.

524
01:02:12,765 --> 01:02:14,699
All right.

525
01:02:23,643 --> 01:02:26,737
Do you hate
normal people ?

526
01:02:28,948 --> 01:02:31,610
Sometimes.

527
01:02:31,684 --> 01:02:33,618
Why?

528
01:02:37,390 --> 01:02:39,324
I suppose...

529
01:02:40,827 --> 01:02:43,159
I'm afraid of them.

530
01:02:45,098 --> 01:02:47,464
Well,

531
01:02:47,533 --> 01:02:51,435
I think you've got
one less person to--

532
01:02:51,504 --> 01:02:53,438
to be afraid of.

533
01:02:58,778 --> 01:03:01,372
[ Gasps ]

534
01:03:16,529 --> 01:03:19,293
Cyclops, you and Storm ready the jet.
I'm gonna find Rogue.

535
01:03:19,365 --> 01:03:22,493
-Jean, get Logan a uniform.
- Whoa, wait a minute.

536
01:03:22,568 --> 01:03:25,560
- He's not coming with us, is he ?
- Yes.

537
01:03:25,638 --> 01:03:28,334
I'm sorry, Professor, but he'll
endanger the mission. And if--

538
01:03:28,408 --> 01:03:31,605
Hey, I wasn't the one who gave
the train station a new sunroof, pal.

539
01:03:31,677 --> 01:03:33,975
- No, you were the one who stabbed Rogue
through the chest.
- Scott--

540
01:03:34,047 --> 01:03:37,448
Hey, why don't you take your
little mission and stick it up your--

541
01:03:37,517 --> 01:03:39,781
Senator Kelly is dead.

542
01:03:41,654 --> 01:03:43,645
I'm going to find her.

543
01:03:45,324 --> 01:03:47,622
Settle this.

544
01:04:25,331 --> 01:04:27,265
I'm sorry.

545
01:04:46,619 --> 01:04:48,553
[ Beeping ]

546
01:04:50,923 --> 01:04:54,689
[ Cyclops ]
You can still hear me, can't you ?

547
01:05:02,268 --> 01:05:07,570
You've taught me everything in my life
that was ever worth knowing.

548
01:05:07,640 --> 01:05:09,225
And if anything happens,

549
01:05:09,225 --> 01:05:10,954
And if anything happens,

550
01:05:11,027 --> 01:05:14,258
well, I'll take care
of them.

551
01:05:27,744 --> 01:05:29,678
Jean ?

552
01:05:33,049 --> 01:05:35,483
Jean !

553
01:05:35,552 --> 01:05:37,850
No !

554
01:05:50,667 --> 01:05:52,601
Jean ?

555
01:05:52,669 --> 01:05:54,603
Jean.

556
01:05:54,671 --> 01:05:57,037
Answer me. Please.

557
01:05:58,274 --> 01:06:00,299
I know
where Magneto's going.

558
01:06:53,763 --> 01:06:55,697
[ Thud,
Man Groaning ]

559
01:07:20,056 --> 01:07:22,251
Magnificent, isn't she ?

560
01:07:23,526 --> 01:07:28,225
- I've seen it.
- I first saw her in 1 949.

561
01:07:28,298 --> 01:07:31,790
America was gonna be
the land of tolerance,

562
01:07:31,868 --> 01:07:33,802
of peace.

563
01:07:38,241 --> 01:07:40,402
Are you going
to kill me ?

564
01:07:45,748 --> 01:07:48,581
- Yes.
- Why ?

565
01:07:48,651 --> 01:07:52,951
Because there is no land of tolerance.
There is no peace.

566
01:07:53,022 --> 01:07:55,786
Not here
or anywhere else.

567
01:07:55,858 --> 01:07:59,692
Women and children,
whole families destroyed...

568
01:07:59,762 --> 01:08:02,595
simply because they were born different
from those in power.

569
01:08:02,665 --> 01:08:07,500
Well, after tonight, the world's
powerful will be just like us.

570
01:08:07,570 --> 01:08:10,630
They will return home
as brothers.

571
01:08:10,707 --> 01:08:13,175
As mutants.

572
01:08:13,242 --> 01:08:15,767
Our cause will be theirs.

573
01:08:15,845 --> 01:08:19,975
Your sacrifice
will mean our survival.

574
01:08:23,720 --> 01:08:27,087
I'll understand if that
comes as small consolation.

575
01:08:30,593 --> 01:08:32,788
Put her in the machine.

576
01:08:34,063 --> 01:08:35,997
I'll raise it.

577
01:08:37,767 --> 01:08:40,861
[ Cyclops ]
Magneto is here. Liberty Island.

578
01:08:40,937 --> 01:08:44,338
Now, presumably, his objective
is to mutate the world leaders
at the U.N. summit...

579
01:08:44,407 --> 01:08:46,466
on Ellis Island.

580
01:08:46,542 --> 01:08:48,703
He doesn't know
his machine kills.

581
01:08:48,778 --> 01:08:52,373
And judging from what the Professor saw,
if Magneto gave Rogue enough power--

582
01:08:52,448 --> 01:08:56,680
[Jean ] He could wipe out everyone
in New York City.

583
01:08:56,753 --> 01:08:59,916
[ Cyclops ] We can insert here
at the George Washington Bridge,

584
01:08:59,989 --> 01:09:02,355
come around the bank
just off of Manhattan.

585
01:09:02,425 --> 01:09:05,986
We land on the far side
of Liberty Island here.

586
01:09:06,062 --> 01:09:08,030
What about harbor patrol ?
Radar ?

587
01:09:08,264 --> 01:09:11,100
If they have anything that can pick up
our jet, they deserve to catch us.

588
01:09:11,100 --> 01:09:11,998
If they have anything that can pick up
our jet, they deserve to catch us.

589
01:09:13,436 --> 01:09:15,370
[ Whirring ]

590
01:09:26,482 --> 01:09:29,508
You actually go outside
in these things ?

591
01:09:29,585 --> 01:09:31,951
Well, what would you prefer,
yellow spandex ?

592
01:09:34,991 --> 01:09:38,188
[ Engines Revving ]

593
01:09:38,261 --> 01:09:41,253
-[ Engines Firing ]
- Whoa !

594
01:10:22,972 --> 01:10:25,964
Okay, there's the bridge.
I'm taking her down.

595
01:10:32,381 --> 01:10:34,941
Storm, some cover,
please.

596
01:10:53,569 --> 01:10:57,232
Toad, Mystique, stay sharp.
We're not alone.

597
01:10:57,306 --> 01:10:59,240
And you stay here.

598
01:10:59,308 --> 01:11:03,074
Once I give my power to the girl,
I'll be temporarily weakened.

599
01:11:03,146 --> 01:11:05,171
You'll be
my only defense.

600
01:11:09,519 --> 01:11:12,682
[ Thunder Rumbles ]

601
01:11:12,755 --> 01:11:14,689
Sounds like
a storm's coming.

602
01:11:29,071 --> 01:11:32,563
- Sorry.
- You call that a landing ?

603
01:11:44,320 --> 01:11:46,254
The torch.

604
01:11:54,297 --> 01:11:56,561
[ Man On TV]
...within a mile of the proceedings.

605
01:11:56,632 --> 01:11:59,396
The first dignitaries
started to arrive about an hour ago,

606
01:11:59,468 --> 01:12:01,834
greeted with a sort
of garden-party atmosphere,

607
01:12:01,904 --> 01:12:03,838
which was designed
to entertain them,

608
01:12:03,906 --> 01:12:06,875
-as the others
traversed the rigid security.
- [ Alarm Wails ]

609
01:12:31,233 --> 01:12:34,999
- [ Sniffs ] There's someone here.
- Where ?

610
01:12:35,070 --> 01:12:38,437
- I don't know. Keep your eye open.
- Logan.

611
01:12:41,509 --> 01:12:44,000
Damn it.

612
01:12:49,885 --> 01:12:52,410
- Anything ?
- I know there's someone here.
I just can't see 'em.

613
01:13:06,968 --> 01:13:08,936
- Wait !
- Wait !

614
01:13:15,377 --> 01:13:17,607
All right, back up.
Back up.

615
01:14:32,620 --> 01:14:34,611
-[Jean Grunting ]
-Jean !

616
01:14:35,957 --> 01:14:38,050
Oh, God.

617
01:15:38,586 --> 01:15:40,781
Don't move.

618
01:15:42,323 --> 01:15:44,348
[ Coughing ]

619
01:15:47,960 --> 01:15:50,588
[ Elevator Bell Rings ]

620
01:15:56,935 --> 01:15:58,869
Don't you people ever die ?

621
01:16:33,305 --> 01:16:36,604
Do you know what happens to a toad
when it's struck by lightning ?

622
01:16:36,675 --> 01:16:38,609
[ Thunder Cracks ]

623
01:16:43,048 --> 01:16:45,482
Same thing that happens
to everything else.

624
01:16:46,652 --> 01:16:48,586
[ Screaming ]

625
01:17:01,121 --> 01:17:03,055
Logan, is that you ?

626
01:17:03,123 --> 01:17:05,057
Shh.

627
01:17:09,996 --> 01:17:11,930
[ Sniffing ]

628
01:17:14,868 --> 01:17:17,996
The other one
ain't far away.

629
01:17:18,071 --> 01:17:20,596
Come on.
We have to regroup.

630
01:17:20,674 --> 01:17:22,608
I know,
but there's a problem.

631
01:17:25,212 --> 01:17:28,079
You're not part of the group.

632
01:17:28,148 --> 01:17:30,912
[ Groaning ]

633
01:17:48,702 --> 01:17:50,693
Hey, hey, it's me.

634
01:17:50,770 --> 01:17:54,171
- Prove it.
- You're a dick.

635
01:17:55,375 --> 01:17:57,309
Okay.

636
01:17:59,012 --> 01:18:01,640
Hey.

637
01:18:18,465 --> 01:18:20,831
[ Logan ]
Everybody get out of here.

638
01:18:20,901 --> 01:18:23,927
- What is it ?
- I can't move.

639
01:18:44,457 --> 01:18:47,153
Ah, my brothers.

640
01:18:47,227 --> 01:18:50,321
Welcome. And, you,

641
01:18:50,397 --> 01:18:53,389
just point those claws of yours
in a safer direction.

642
01:19:07,480 --> 01:19:09,505
You'd better close
your eyes.

643
01:19:12,619 --> 01:19:14,917
-[ Cyclops ] Storm, fry him.
-[ Magneto ] Oh,yes.

644
01:19:14,988 --> 01:19:19,891
A bolt of lightning into
a huge copper conductor.

645
01:19:19,960 --> 01:19:21,951
I thought you lived
at a school.

646
01:19:22,028 --> 01:19:24,462
[ Applause ]

647
01:19:27,033 --> 01:19:30,594
For those of you who may not be familiar
with the historical significance--

648
01:19:30,670 --> 01:19:33,696
[ People Translating ]

649
01:19:35,842 --> 01:19:38,606
Mystique ?

650
01:19:38,678 --> 01:19:40,771
- Mystique ?
- I've seen Senator Kelly.

651
01:19:42,616 --> 01:19:46,313
So the good senator
survived his fall...

652
01:19:46,386 --> 01:19:48,786
and the swim to shore.

653
01:19:48,855 --> 01:19:51,085
He's become even more powerful
than I could have imagined.

654
01:19:51,157 --> 01:19:53,853
- He's dead.
-[ Storm ] It's true.

655
01:19:53,927 --> 01:19:58,455
I saw him die.
Like those people down there will die.

656
01:19:58,531 --> 01:20:02,160
Are you sure
you saw what you saw ?

657
01:20:02,235 --> 01:20:06,604
I would also like to thank
the president of the United States...

658
01:20:06,673 --> 01:20:08,937
for hosting this event...

659
01:20:09,009 --> 01:20:12,410
under the lights of
the great city of New York.

660
01:20:19,753 --> 01:20:23,519
Why do none of you understand
what I'm trying to do ?

661
01:20:23,590 --> 01:20:29,358
Those people down there,
they control our fate and
the fate of every other mutant.

662
01:20:30,764 --> 01:20:33,028
Well,

663
01:20:33,099 --> 01:20:35,761
soon our fate
will be theirs.

664
01:20:35,835 --> 01:20:39,100
[ Rogue ]
Help! Please help me!

665
01:20:39,172 --> 01:20:41,106
You're so full of shit.

666
01:20:41,174 --> 01:20:45,372
If you were really so righteous,
it'd be you in that thing.

667
01:20:47,247 --> 01:20:51,047
Help!
Somebody help me!

668
01:21:03,797 --> 01:21:05,731
[ Rogue ]
Please!

669
01:21:05,799 --> 01:21:10,827
-[ Growls ]
-Somebody please help me!

670
01:21:14,741 --> 01:21:17,073
-Somebody!
- [ Grunting ]

671
01:21:17,143 --> 01:21:19,737
Help--

672
01:21:27,220 --> 01:21:30,747
- [ Yells ]
- Logan !

673
01:21:32,292 --> 01:21:34,954
[ Door Opens ]

674
01:22:27,596 --> 01:22:30,963
- I'm sorry, my dear.
- Don't do this.

675
01:22:43,379 --> 01:22:45,472
This is mine.

676
01:23:11,407 --> 01:23:13,466
[ Rogue Screaming ]

677
01:23:48,377 --> 01:23:50,504
You owe me a scream.

678
01:23:53,816 --> 01:23:56,546
Hey, bub. I'm not
finished with you yet.

679
01:23:59,622 --> 01:24:02,284
-[ Rogue Screams ]
-Jean.

680
01:24:02,358 --> 01:24:04,792
- Scott, when I tell you,
open your eyes.
- No.

681
01:24:04,860 --> 01:24:07,351
- Trust me.
- You drop something ?

682
01:24:11,901 --> 01:24:14,028
Now.

683
01:24:28,050 --> 01:24:30,245
- Thanks.
- Don't mention it.

684
01:24:30,319 --> 01:24:34,346
We gotta get her out of there.
Cyclops, can you hit it ?

685
01:24:34,423 --> 01:24:37,586
-[ Cyclops ] The rings are
too fast. I'll kill her.
-[ Logan ] Just shoot it.

686
01:24:37,660 --> 01:24:39,992
- Storm, can you get me up there ?
- I can't control it like that.

687
01:24:40,062 --> 01:24:42,929
- You could fly right over the torch.
- Then let me go.

688
01:24:42,998 --> 01:24:47,367
If I don't make it, then at least
you can still blast the damn thing.

689
01:24:48,604 --> 01:24:50,868
All right, do it.

690
01:24:50,940 --> 01:24:53,408
Jean, use your power.
Try to steady him.

691
01:24:54,810 --> 01:24:57,074
Hang on to something.

692
01:25:50,833 --> 01:25:52,926
Scott, wait.

693
01:26:23,565 --> 01:26:25,965
- I have to.
-Just wait.

694
01:26:27,836 --> 01:26:30,430
I have a shot.

695
01:26:30,506 --> 01:26:32,371
I'm taking it.

696
01:27:12,268 --> 01:27:14,202
Come on.

697
01:28:45,160 --> 01:28:47,924
Hey, this one's alive.
Let's get him out of here.

698
01:29:14,023 --> 01:29:15,957
Welcome back.

699
01:29:16,025 --> 01:29:19,085
I knew you'd find
your way.

700
01:29:19,161 --> 01:29:21,254
I had you to guide me.

701
01:29:23,499 --> 01:29:25,558
How did we do ?

702
01:29:53,028 --> 01:29:55,758
Oh !
Oh, that tickles.

703
01:29:56,932 --> 01:29:58,866
Hey.

704
01:30:00,336 --> 01:30:02,270
Hey.

705
01:30:02,338 --> 01:30:05,603
- How're you feeling ?
- Fantastic.

706
01:30:07,676 --> 01:30:10,042
That was
a brave thing you did.

707
01:30:11,447 --> 01:30:15,042
- Did it work ?
- Yeah. She's fine.

708
01:30:16,719 --> 01:30:19,950
She took on a few of your more
charming personality traits for a while.

709
01:30:20,022 --> 01:30:23,617
- [ Chuckles, Coughing ]
- But we lived through it.

710
01:30:27,096 --> 01:30:30,031
I think she's
a little taken with you.

711
01:30:30,099 --> 01:30:34,502
Well, you can tell her
my heart belongs to someone else.

712
01:30:38,907 --> 01:30:42,741
- You know, you and I--
- How's the professor ?

713
01:30:45,547 --> 01:30:48,516
- He's good.
- Good.

714
01:30:54,723 --> 01:30:58,989
There's an abandoned military compound
